# üß≠ Unraid Setup

<p align="center">
  <img width="1101" height="238" alt="unraid-banner" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b14165f4-24ff-4abe-8af6-3ca852e781d4" />
</p>

This guide walks you through deploying NzbDAV on Unraid using Docker, rclone, and the User Scripts plugin. It ensures consistent access to your media via WebDAV across Sonarr, Radarr, Plex, and other containers.

---

## üîå Required Plugins

Install the following via Community Applications:

- `rclone` ‚Äì for WebDAV mounting  
- `User Scripts` ‚Äì to automate startup tasks

---

## üê≥ Docker Container

Install the **NzbDAV** container from the Unraid App Store. It should expose a WebDAV endpoint (e.g., `http://localhost:8080/`).

---

## üìÅ Directory Structure

Create the following directories via terminal or Unraid file manager:

```bash
mkdir -p /mnt/user/nzbdav/mount
mkdir -p /mnt/user/nzbdav/media/movies
mkdir -p /mnt/user/nzbdav/media/tv
```

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è rclone Configuration

Go to **Settings > rclone** in Unraid and add the following remote:

```ini
[nzb-dav]
type = webdav
url = http://<your-endpoint>
vendor = other
user = <your-webdav-user>
pass = <your-obscured-password>
```

To generate the password securely:

```bash
rclone obscure 'your-password'
```

More info: [rclone obscure](https://rclone.org/commands/rclone_obscure)

---

## üì¶ Container Path Mapping

Update volume mappings for **all containers** (including `NzbDAV`, `Sonarr`, `Radarr`, `Plex`, etc.):

```
Host Path: /mnt/user/nzbdav
Container Path: /mnt/user/nzbdav
```

This ensures consistent access to:

- WebDAV mount: `/mnt/user/nzbdav/mount`
- Media folders:
  - Movies: `/mnt/user/nzbdav/media/movies`
  - TV Shows: `/mnt/user/nzbdav/media/tv`

---

## üöÄ Startup Script

Create a new script in the **User Scripts plugin** and set it to run at **Array Start**. Paste the following:

```bash
#!/bin/bash

# === SETTINGS ===
RCLONE_REMOTE_PATH="nzb-dav:"
MOUNT_POINT="/mnt/user/nzbdav/mount"
CACHE_PATH="/dev/shm"
REMOTE_NAME="NzbDAV"
WAIT_TIME=10
DOCKER_CONTAINERS=( "sonarrnzb" "radarrnzb" "plex" )

sleep "$WAIT_TIME"

echo "üöÄ Starting nzbdav container..."
docker start "$REMOTE_NAME"

echo "üîç Checking if $REMOTE_NAME is running..."
if docker ps --filter "name=$REMOTE_NAME" --filter "status=running" | grep -q "$REMOTE_NAME"; then
    echo "‚úÖ $REMOTE_NAME is running."
else
    echo "‚ùå $REMOTE_NAME failed to start. Exiting."
    exit 1
fi

echo "‚è≥ Waiting $WAIT_TIME seconds for $REMOTE_NAME to be ready..."
sleep "$WAIT_TIME"

echo "üìÇ Mounting WebDAV to $MOUNT_POINT..."
mkdir -p "$MOUNT_POINT"

if mountpoint -q "$MOUNT_POINT"; then
    echo "üîÑ Unmounting existing mount..."
    fusermount -u "$MOUNT_POINT"
fi

rclone mount "$RCLONE_REMOTE_PATH" "$MOUNT_POINT" \
  --vfs-read-ahead=256M \
  --vfs-read-chunk-size=64M \
  --vfs-read-chunk-size-limit=4G \
  --vfs-cache-mode=full \
  --vfs-cache-max-age=3h \
  --vfs-cache-max-size=25G \
  --buffer-size=64M \
  --dir-cache-time=1s \
  --log-file=/var/log/rclone-nzbdav.log \
  --cache-dir="$CACHE_PATH" \
  --allow-other \
  --links \
  --use-cookies \
  --uid=1000 \
  --gid=1000 &

sleep 2

if mountpoint -q "$MOUNT_POINT"; then
    echo "‚úÖ WebDAV mounted successfully."
else
    echo "‚ùå Failed to mount WebDAV."
    exit 1
fi

echo "üì¶ Starting specified Docker containers..."
for container in "${DOCKER_CONTAINERS[@]}"; do
    echo "‚ñ∂Ô∏è Starting $container..."
    docker start "$container"
done

echo "üéâ All tasks completed."
```

---

## ‚úÖ Final Checks

- Confirm `/mnt/user/nzbdav/mount` is populated  
- Ensure Sonarr, Radarr, and Plex can access the media folders  
- Check logs at `/var/log/rclone-nzbdav.log` for troubleshooting

---

Let me know if you'd like to add healthchecks, auto-remount logic, or tagging support for media formats!
